# Rescue PWAs installed against the old content-addressed manifest.
# The manifest URL was once hashed under `/_build/assets/`; installed
# clients persist that URL and re-fetch it on their own schedule, so
# after a redeploy (new hash, old file gone) they'd 404. The manifest
# now lives at a stable `/manifest.webmanifest`, and this 301 forwards
# any straggler still pinned to a hashed path. `_redirects` rules fire
# regardless of whether an asset matches, so this works even though no
# such file exists anymore. Removable once old installs age out.
/_build/assets/manifest-*  /manifest.webmanifest  301

# Serve a route-shaped prerendered shell for dynamic client routes so
# a direct hit (refresh, shared link) hydrates instead of 404ing.
# Target must match the *route* the client will mount, not the URL
# tree's index — otherwise hydration walks SSR DOM produced by a
# different route and blows up. `/studio/__landing/` resolves to the
# `[id]` route with id `__landing`; the page renders its loading
# fallback during prerender, which is what the client first paints
# too. Status 200 = rewrite (proxy target's content, keep original
# URL). Trailing slash is required: with the default
# `html_handling = "auto-trailing-slash"`, omitting it makes
# Cloudflare 301 to the canonical folder URL, which leaks the
# sentinel id into the address bar.

/studio/:id  /studio/__landing/  200
